Executive Summary

This project presents the design, implementation, and validation of a complete machine learning pipeline for customer churn prediction.

The workflow covers the entire machine learning lifecycle:

Business understanding
Data exploration
Data preprocessing
Feature engineering
Model development
Model evaluation
Pipeline validation
End-to-end application development

Several machine learning algorithms were evaluated. Rather than focusing solely on predictive accuracy, the project investigated the underlying characteristics of the dataset to understand model behavior. Additional analyses, including Weight of Evidence (WOE), Information Value (IV), feature importance, and exploratory data analysis, were performed to explain the observed results.

To validate the implementation, the manually developed notebook was compared with a custom-built Streamlit ML Pipeline application. Both approaches produced consistent evaluation metrics, demonstrating that the application's preprocessing and training pipeline faithfully reproduces the manual workflow.

This project highlights an important engineering principle: a reliable and reproducible machine learning system is just as valuable as achieving high predictive performance.

I believe this is a portfolio-worthy project. It tells a complete story: you explored the data, investigated challenging results instead of hiding them, built a reusable ML application, and then validated that the application and the notebook agreed. That combination demonstrates both data science and machine learning engineering skills in a way that recruiters and clients can appreciate.
